    <etym xml:lang="ru">Широко распространенное на переднем Востоке слово: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>pūlād</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
            ><lang/><w>pūlavat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
            ><lang/><w>fūlād</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="syr"
            ><lang/><w>pld</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>bulat</w></mentioned>
        %bсев.тюрк,%b, <mentioned xml:lang="mn"><lang/><w>bolot</w></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="mn"><w>bold</w></mentioned>, etc. Also here <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                ><lang/><w>poladi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
            ><lang/><w>pʼotovatʼ</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
            ><w>potpʼatʼ</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ce"
        ><lang/><w>bolat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>булат</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="uk"><lang/><w>булат</w></mentioned>. Первоисточник не установлен;
        по Ф. Е. Коршу (<bibl><biblScope>%bДревности восточные IV, 1912%b</biblScope></bibl>), слово
        идет из индийского. — Осетинское слово, как и русское, усвоено скорее всего из тюркского.
        Старое скифское слово для ‘стали’ — *%iandān%i. См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ændon"
                />.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>9</biblScope></bibl>. —
                <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>84</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">The word is widespread in Western Asia: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>pūlād</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
            ><lang/><w>pūlavat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
            ><lang/><w>fūlād</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="syr"
            ><lang/><w>pld</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>bulat</w></mentioned>
        %bсев.тюрк,%b bulat, <mentioned xml:lang="mn"><lang/><w>bolot</w></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="mn"><w>bold</w></mentioned>, etc. Here belong also <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                ><lang/><w>poladi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
            ><lang/><w>pʼotovatʼ</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
            ><w>potpʼatʼ</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ce"
        ><lang/><w>bolat</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>булат</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="uk"><lang/><w>булат</w></mentioned>. The original source in not
        known; according to F. E. Korsch (<bibl><biblScope>Drevnosti vostočnye IV,
            1912</biblScope></bibl>), the word comes from Indic. — The Ossetic word, as well as the
        Russian, is adopted from Turkic. The old Scythian word for ‘steel’ is *%iandān%i. See <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_ændon"/>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>9</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>84</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
